“PGP” “Pretty Good Privacy”; “GPG” “Gnu Privacy Guard.”
it was the original freeware copyrighted program, GPG is the re-write of PGP.
PGP uses the RSA algorithm and the IDEA encryption algorithm.
GPG uses the NIST AES, Advanced Encryption Standard.

you make Public_key or Private_key
you give out "Public_key" to people who want to send you message and they "Encrypt" the message with your Public_key 
and when you get that message you "Decrypt" the message using your "Private_key"

sudo gpg --full-gen-key  - generate key pairs
gpg -r email -e "file"   -r means recipient  - Encrypt
gpg -d "file"            - Decrypt  
